title: Art Centers of the World - Rome (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Art Centers of the World: Rome
The World Publishing Company | 1968 | English | 218 pages | PDF | 18.6 MB

Art centers of the world, a series of books under the general editorship of G. S. Whittet, IS designed to give the tourist and the art lover a detailed guide to the major museums and commercial galleries of each city Rome, the fourth in the series, presents the reader with a sound non-academic approach to painting and sculpture in the city - all of which can be seen in the permanent collections and art galleries But, unlike other cities, museums in Rome are seldom furnished with room-by-room guides and here for the first time is a book which provides an up-to-date necessary aid. A section entitled 'Out of doors and incidentals deals particularly with sculpture adorning the squares, parks and street corners of Rome
